posts.title: How you may lose your U.S. citizenship
posts.content:
You may lose your U.S. citizenship in specific cases, including if you:

  • Run for public office in a foreign country (under certain conditions)
  • Enter military service in a foreign country (under certain conditions)
  • Apply for citizenship in a foreign country with the intention of giving up U.S. citizenship
  • Commit an act of treason against the United States
  • Are a naturalized U.S. citizen who faces denaturalization due to committing certain crimes

Any deepstaters that refuse to testify to Congress about their involvement in subversive activities may lose their citizenship. This is different from others getting 'contempt of congress' because those subpoenas weren't about subversive anti-government activities, but rather about implicating them in an accessory to alleged crimes (fake / political / nebulous/vague crimes that were never charged and/or to which the accused was immune by sovereign immunity). So Steve Bannon and Dr. Navarro for example were not subpoenaed for 'subversive' or treasonous reasons--it was a witch hunt.

2

Those Antifa people that fought in Ukraine may lose their citizenship under Trump. Those that acted to impeach Trump for doing what the President is not only legally allowed to do, but MANDATED to do ('perfect call with Zelenskyy'), can lose their citizenship under Trump (all the congresspeople), since this is an act of seditious conspiracy to undermine the US government.

3

The Vindmans might lose their US citizenship if they are given any money by the Ukranian government, because they are Ukranian-Americans. Same with Victoria Nuland.

349(a)(4) - accepting employment with a foreign government after the age of 18 if (a) one has the nationality of that foreign state or (b) an oath or declaration of allegiance is required in accepting the position;

4

Those illegal immigrants and legal immigrants and asylees that joined ANTIFA, BLM, Sunrise, Patriots front or other violent, subversive, extremist groups can lose any citizenship they obtained if they joined within 5 yrs of their naturalization.

You had better believe that if the Trump adminstration 1 had greatly increased 'denaturalization' / 'expatriation' of citizens, Trump admin 2 is going to quadruple down their efforts.

Finally, very funny how my CPU goes nuts and my typing slows when I write these essay posts. Very over-the-targetty. You feds sound scared, bros. That you have to panopticon my every keypress. Stickbundles. The whole lot of you.

  • https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/legal/travel-legal-considerations/Relinquishing-US-Nationality.html
  • https://www.usa.gov/renounce-lose-citizenship
